# Hybrid mobile UI preferences

## Scope

- Mobile remodeled views ship under **`MOBILE_BROWSE_V2`** at **`max-width: 960px`** (`src/style.mobile-browse.css` + `isMobileBrowse()` in `main.js`).
- **Desktop layouts stay unchanged** unless the user explicitly asks to change them.
- Prefer implementing against established patterns over new HTML mockups when the direction is clear.

## Visual tokens

- Dark Hybrid console: `--bg #0b0d0e`, accent `--accent #ffb454`.
- Grid / box separators use **`--sep-line`** (muted accent), including outer edges — not full-bright accent bars.
- Fonts: JetBrains Mono (data/labels), Oswald / Archivo / Inter Tight as already wired — do not fall back to Inter/Roboto/system stacks for new UI.

## Compare (mobile)

- **Column-snap sheet** (former Mock B): sticky property gutter + equal metal columns; drag headers to reorder; no ←/→ buttons.
- Bottom-sheet “Add metal” (no native `<select>`).
- Temps: °C by default; tap a temp cell to toggle all to °F (`state.compareTempUnit`).

## Table (mobile)

- **Four-column sheet**: Element | Melting | Density | Conductivity.
- Element column width follows the **longest name** in the current filter; numeric columns share remaining width.
- Center header labels and numeric values; spell out headers (no σ).
- No summary column on mobile.
- Header taps sort: Element → `name`, Melting → `meltingDesc`, Density → `densityDesc`, Conductivity → `conductivityDesc`.
- Row tap → encyclopedia entry (`mobilePane = "entry"`); defer re-render so the tap does not hit view tabs.

## Navigation (mobile)

- Series title bar: **‹** back → Metals by series hub (`openSeriesHub`).
- Entry detail: **‹** back → card list (not series).

## Series hub (mobile)

- **2-column** series tile grid at ≤960px (not 3). Cap media/desc height (~7.5rem); drop the desktop `min-height: 280px` tower.
- **All metals** tile last, full width.

## Cleanup

- Do not reintroduce `mockups/` HTML for Compare/Table unless the user asks for side-by-side design exploration again.
